<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-sgqXBX21p7aDzPa97WQZkw" name=",_NFFzcJZ4EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" guid="-sgqXBX21p7aDzPa97WQZkw" changeDate="2011-07-08T05:14:24.610-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The potential hazards and operational scenarios are analyzed for the item before any safety mechanisms are applied.&#xD;
    Safety mechanisms intended to be implemented or that have already been implemented in legacy systems shall not be&#xD;
    considered as means for providing risk reduction.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Common techniques for this sort of analysis are Failure Modes Effects Analysis (FMEA) and Fault Tree Analysis (FTA).&#xD;
    Model based techniques are available to be used for this process see &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.tech.real_time.safe_rel_analysis.base-ibm/guidances/practices/safe_rel_an_966E315A.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_2BtTQLePEd-05egMquN4Dg&quot;>Safety and Reliability Analysis&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For a detailed explanation of this&amp;nbsp;task it is advised that the user refers to ISO 26262, volume 3, clause 7.4.4&#xD;
    and Annex B1, Hazard analysis and risk assessment, in Volume 3.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_03IIsJZ5EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Capture operational situations and modes that could lead to hazardous behaviour" guid="_03IIsJZ5EeCPtY0LnWkRDw"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_DArdUJZ6EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Create a list of operational scenarios and situations to be evaluated" guid="_DArdUJZ6EeCPtY0LnWkRDw"/>
  <sections xmi:id="_Mj6uIJZ6EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Determine potential hazards systematically" guid="_Mj6uIJZ6EeCPtY0LnWkRDw">
    <sectionDescription>Hazards shall be defined in terms of the conditions or events that can be observed at the vehicle level.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_RmYicJZ6EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Idenfity consequences of the hazardours events based upon the relevant operational modes and situations" guid="_RmYicJZ6EeCPtY0LnWkRDw"/>
  <purpose>To understand the potential hazards and failures that could occur or be caused by the item.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
